MOST IMMEDIAPE
No. 1/34/1/2011-Cab(i).
GOVERNMENT OF INDIA (BHARAT SARKAR)
CABINET SECRETARIAT (MANTRIMANDAL SACHIVALAYA)
New Delhi, the 12th July, 2011
The undersigned is directed to say that with effect from the 12th July, 2011:-
(i)
The Prime Minister relinquished the charge of the office of the Minister of Raiiways;
(ii)
Shri Vilasrao Deshmukh relinquished the charge of the office of the Minister of Rural
Development and the office of the Minister of Panchayati Raj and assumed the
charge of the office of the Minister of Science and Technology and the charge of the
office of the Minister of Earth Sciences;
(ii)
Shri M. Veerappa Moily relinquished the charge of the office of the Minister of Law
and Justice and assumed the charge of the office of the Minister of Corporate
Affairs;
Shri Dayanidhi Maran relinquished the charge of the office of the Minister of
Textiles;
(iv)
(v)
Shri Murli Deora relinquished the charge of the office of the Minister of Corporate
Affairs;
(vi)
Shri B.K. Handique relinquished the charge of the office of the Minister of
Development of North Eastern Region;
Shri Anand Sharma assumed the additional charge of the office of the Minister of
Textiles. He will continue to hold the charge of the office of the Minister of
Commerce and Industry;
(vii)
(viii)
Dr. M.S. Gill relinquished the charge of the office of the Minister of Statistics and
Programme Implementation;
(ix)
Shri Pawan Kumar Bansal relinquished the charge of the office of the Minister of
Science and Technology and the office of the Minister of Earth Sciences and
assumed the additional charge of the office of the Minister of Water Resources. He
will continue to hold the charge of the office of the Minister of Parliamentary Affairs;
Shri Kantilal Bhuria relinquished the charge of the office of the Minister of Tribal
Affairs;
(x)
Shri Salman Khursheed relinquished the charge of the office of the Minister of Water
Resources and assumed the charge of the office of the Minister of Law and Justice.
He will continue to hold the additional charge of the office of the Minister of Minority
Affairs;
(xi)
(xii)
Shri Jairam Ramesh relinquished the charge of the office of the Minister of State
(Independent Charge) of the Ministry of Environment and Forests and assumed the
charge of the office of the Minister of Rural Development;
(xiii) Shri Beni Prasad Verma relinquished the charge of the office of the Minister of State
(Independent Charge) of the Ministry of Steel and assumed the charge of the office
of the Minister of Steel;
(xiv) Shri Dinesh Trivedi relinquished the charge of the office of the Minister of State in
the Ministry of Health and Family Welfare and assumed the charge of the office of
the Minister of Railways;
(xv)
Shri V. Kishore Chandra Deo assumed the charge of the office of the Minister of
Tribal Affairs and the office of the Minister of Panchayati Raj;
(xvi) Shri Srikant Jena assumed the charge of the office of the Minister of State
(Independent Charge) of the Ministry of Statistics and Programme Implementation.
He will continue to hold the charge of the office of the Minister of State in the
Ministry of Chemicals and Fertilizers;
(xvii) Shri Gurudas Kamat relinquished the charge of the office of the Minister of State in
the Ministry of Home Affairs and the office of the Minister of State in the Ministry of
Communications and Information Technology and assumed the charge of the office
of the Minister of State (Independent Charge) of the Ministry of Drinking Water and
Sanitation;

(xviii) Smt. Jayanthi Natarajan assumed the charge of the office of the Minister of State
(Independent Charge) of the Ministry of Environment and Forests;
(xix) Shri Paban Singh Ghatowar assumed the charge of the office of the Minister of
State (Independent Charge) of the Ministry of Development of North Eastern
Region;
(xx)
Shri E. Ahamed assumed the charge of the office of the Minister of State in the
Ministry of Human Resource Development. He will continue to hold the charge of
the office of the Minister of State in the Ministry of External Affairs;
(xxi) Shri V. Narayanasamy relinquished the charge of the office of the Minister of State
in the Ministry of Parliamentary Affairs. He will continue to hold the charge of the
office of the Minister of State in the Ministry of Personnel, Public Grievances and
Pensions and the office of the Minister of State in the Prime Minister's Office;
(xxii) Shri A. Sai Prathap relinquished the charge of the office of the Minister of State in
the Ministry of Heavy Industries and Public Enterprises;
(xxiii) Shri Harish Rawat assumed the charge of the office of the Minister of State in the
Ministry of Parliamentary Affairs. He will continue to hold the charge of the office of
the Minister of State in the Ministry of Agriculture and the office of the Minister of
State in the Ministry of Food Processing Industries;
(xxiv) Shri Mukul Roy relinquished the additional charge of the office of the Minister of
State in the Ministry of Railways. He will continue to hold the charge of the office of
the Minister of State in the Ministry of Shipping;
(xxv) Shri Arun Yadav relinquished the charge of the office of the Minister of State in the
Ministry of Agriculture and the office of the Minister of State in the Ministry of Food
Processing Industries;
(xxvi) Shri Ashwani Kumar relinquished the charge of the office of the Minister of State in
the Ministry of Parliamentary Affairs. He will continue to hold the charge of the office
of the Minister of State in the Ministry of Planning, the office of the Minister of State
in the Ministry of Science and Technology and the office of the Minister of State in
the Ministry of Earth Sciences;
(Xxvii) Shri Sudip Bandyopadhyay assumed the charge of the office of the Minister of State
in the Ministry of Health and Family Welfare;
(Xxviii) Shri Charan Das Mahant assumed the charge of the office of the Minister of State in
the Ministry of Agriculture and the office of the Minister of State in the Ministry of
Food Processing Industries;
(xxix) Shri Jitendra Singh assumed the charge of the office of the Minister of State in the
Ministry of Home Affairs;
(Xxx) Shri Milind Deora assumed the charge of the office of the Minister
Ministry of Communications and Information Technology; and

Ministry of Parliamentary Affairs.

Gazette Notification.
